The paper focuses on security threats in mobile edge computing, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed model uses deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The model also uses location information, which is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of unsupervised learning in the proposed model suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
